 measuring cup and mix <b>40 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl using spatula."},{"content":"Add ricotta cheese, 300 g reserved grated cheese, eggs, salt and black pepper and mix <b>40 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a disposable icing bag or freezer bag and allow to cool for a few minutes."},{"content":"Cut a hole in the piping bag to the same diameter as the dried cannelloni tubes and fill them with stuffing mixture. Arrange filled cannelloni in greased Varoma dish and tray, leaving a little space between them and lightly brush the cannelloni with extra virgin olive oil to avoid sticking. Clean mixing bowl."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Have you ever imagined steaming cannelloni in your Varoma? The steam tenderises the pasta beautifully. Serve this tasty dish to both vegetarians and meat-lovers (who may not notice the lack of meat), then feel free to use this recipe as a starting point to create your own special version – see our variations to help you get started.","Frozen artichoke hearts can be used instead of fresh or canned.","<strong>Mushroom cannelloni:<\/strong> replace artichokes with <b>400 g sliced<b> fresh mushrooms. In <b>step 3<b> add mushrooms and white wine and cook without measuring cup <b><strong>15 min\/100°C\/speed 1.<\/strong><b> Drain mushroom mixture through simmering basket, return drained mixture to mixing bowl and continue recipe from <b>step 4.<b>","For meat-lovers, add <b>100 g pancetta<b> or bacon cubes in <b>step 4.<b>"],"basicInfo":["medium","45m","1h 35m","4 portions"]}